full_text:
The Reds are 11th in MLB in runs scored (27) despite being:

-Last in avg. exit velo, hard-hit%, and xwOBA
-29th in wRC+ and K%
-28th in wOBA
-27th in AVG, OBP, BB%
-25th in SLG
No denying that Mike Moustakas has looked downright awful at the plate so far. He's now 1-for-17 with 9 strikeouts and no walks.
